snippet: Political divisions within the elected General National Congress, with groups backed by rival militias, have rendered the appointed government almost powerless.
abstract: Political killings continue to plague Libya in aftermath of 2011 revolution that ousted Col Muammar el-Qadaffi from power, with over 1,200 people killed nationwide in two years; political divisions within elected General National Congress have left it unstable and powerless to bring order.
lead_paragraph: Political divisions within the elected General National Congress, with groups backed by rival militias, have rendered the appointed government almost powerless.
